// Texas regulatory obligations — TRANSPORTATION / SHUTTLE (intrastate for-hire). Encoded from
// docs/rules-research/texas/transportation.md (verified 2026-07-07). The Texas intrastate track: TxDMV
// registration and the $500k/$5M intrastate insurance tiers attach when operatesIntrastate = true —
// NOT when "operatesInterstate = false": the 643.002 exemption excuses only carriers operating
// EXCLUSIVELY in interstate commerce, so a MIXED carrier (both true) owes BOTH layers (CONF-23, v1.2).
// The Texas CDL implements the federal CDL floor (satisfiesFederal), so the federal CDL is not double-
// emitted. The intrastate medical certificate is 'probable' (DPS primary sources were down) and defers to
// the verified federal medical-examiner-certificate in production.
// KNOWN SCOPE PROXY (recorded, CONF-24): applicability encodes only the passenger-capacity prong of the
// 548.001 CMV definition; the weight (>26,000 lb), hazmat, school-bus and household-goods prongs have no
// frozen fact and are out of v1 scope — a heavy (>26,000 lb) vehicle seating 15 or fewer is NOT covered
// by these gates. Documented in SCHEMA v1 KNOWN LIMITATIONS.
